Key Match Events: Mitch Marsh scored an unbeaten 177 from 132 balls
Marnus Labuschagne effected two smart run outs in Bangladesh's innings
Adam Zampa took the key wicket of Liton Das (36)
Miscellaneous Highlights: The win ensures Australia will enter Thursday's semi-final against South Africa as one of the competition's form teams
Others: Seve Smith also struck a timely 63 not out ahead of big selection call for the semi-finals
Josh Hazlewood (0-21 from seven overs) also bowled well
Sean Abbott took 2-61 in his first World Cup match after being called in for the rested Mitchell Starc
